placeDesc: The Nook may be famous for its cheese-stuffed “Juicy Lucy” burger, but have you seen the basement? An old train car sits in this basement bowling alley, adorned with over $16,000 worth of one dollar bills. Patrons decorate the bills and tack them up on the ceiling and walls with toothpicks. Sharpies are provided.
placeShortDesc: The basement bowling alley of this St. Paul dive bar is decorated with thousands of dollar bills.
placeNearby: Center for Lost Objects,F. Scott Fitzgerald House,Ax-Man Surplus
placeAddress: 492 Hamline Ave S,Saint Paul, Minnesota,United States
